<doc id="629267" wikidata="Q5100439" url="?curid=629267" title="Chinese Domain Name Consortium">
<text>The Chinese Domain Name Consortium, created on 19 May 2000, is a collaboration among the People&#x27;s Republic of China, the Republic of China (Taiwan), Hong Kong and Macau to come up with a standard way to create a domain name system for Chinese characters.

